---
import DefaultLayout from '@layouts/DefaultLayout.astro'
import PageHeader from '@components/PageHeader.astro'
import { Accordion, AccordionItem, Badge } from 'accessible-astro-components'
import Feature from '@components/Feature.astro'
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components'
---

<DefaultLayout title="About">
  <PageHeader
    title="About"
    subtitle="Learn more about our mission to create a safer digital environment. Dive into our learning modules designed to teach individuals about digital citizenship, authentication, data privacy, and more."
    bgType="bordered"
  />

  <section class="mb-12">
    <div class="container">

      <!-- Intro Section -->
      <div class="section-title mt-[3.5rem] flex items-center gap-4 sm:gap-6">
        <div class="section-badge">
          <Badge class="section-icon"><Icon class="m-3" name="lucide:book-open" /></Badge>
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
          <h2 class="section-heading">Our Mission</h2>
          <p class="section-subtitle">Empowering individuals through digital education.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 mb-12" style="font-size: 1.15rem; line-height: 1.8; color: var(--color-neutral-700);">
        <p class="mb-6">
          Today’s world is more connected than ever. The internet, smartphones, games, and social media help us learn, create, and stay in touch with others. But being online also comes with risks — especially for children. That’s why it’s so important for young people to understand the basics of cybersecurity and learn how to stay safe in the digital world.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6">
          As technology becomes a natural part of everyday life, children need simple and practical guidance on how to protect their personal information, recognize online threats, and make smart decisions online. Cybersecurity is no longer just for experts — it’s a life skill for everyone.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6">
          One of the biggest challenges in teaching cybersecurity is that many educators are not trained specialists in this field. They often lack easy-to-use, adaptable materials that would help them explain complex topics in a clear and age-appropriate way. Without the right tools and support, it can be difficult to bring cybersecurity education into classrooms effectively.
        </p>
        <p class="mb-6">
          Our goal is to close this gap by providing accessible, engaging resources designed specifically for educators and children. By supporting teachers with ready-to-use materials and practical guidance, we help ensure that young people gain the knowledge, confidence, and skills they need to explore the digital world safely and responsibly.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Values Section -->
      <div class="section-title mt-[3.5rem] flex items-center gap-4 sm:gap-6" id="our-values">
        <div class="section-badge">
          <Badge class="section-icon"><Icon class="m-3" name="lucide:star" /></Badge>
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
          <h2 class="section-heading">Our Core Values</h2>
          <p class="section-subtitle">The principles that guide our platform and community.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 gap-8 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-2 mt-8 mb-16 feature-card feature-content value-grid">
        <Feature class="value-feature" icon="lucide:heart" title="Scalable Impact">
          <p class="mt-4">Our train-the-trainer approach makes cybersecurity education easy to expand and adapt. It helps reach more schools, educators, and children across Europe.</p>
        </Feature>
        <Feature class="value-feature" icon="lucide:shield-check" title="International Collaboration">
          <p class="mt-4">The project goes beyond national borders, connecting countries and institutions to build a shared approach to cybersecurity education.</p>
        </Feature>
        <Feature class="value-feature" icon="lucide:lightbulb" title="Practical & Adaptable">
          <p class="mt-4">Designed for real classrooms, our hybrid model provides flexible and ready-to-use solutions that fit diverse educational environments.</p>
        </Feature>
        <Feature class="value-feature" icon="lucide:users" title="European Digital Cohesion">
          <p class="mt-4">Aligned with the EU digital framework, the project supports a consistent and harmonized standard of cybersecurity education across Europe while encouraging the exchange of best practices.</p>
        </Feature>
      </div>
      
      <!-- FAQ Section -->
      <div class="section-title mt-[3.5rem] flex items-center gap-4 sm:gap-6" id="faq">
        <div class="section-badge">
          <Badge class="section-icon"><Icon class="m-3" name="lucide:help-circle" /></Badge>
        </div>
        <div class="flex-1 min-w-0">
          <h2 class="section-heading">FAQ</h2>
          <p class="section-subtitle">Everything you need to know about the platform.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8">
        <Accordion>
          <AccordionItem class="mb-4" title="What is the primary goal?" variant="chevron">
            Our primary goal is to make cybersecurity education accessible, practical, and scalable across Europe. We aim to equip educators with ready-to-use tools and training so they can confidently teach children how to stay safe online. By using a train-the-trainer model and adaptable learning materials, the project ensures that cybersecurity knowledge can reach diverse classrooms and educational systems.
          </AccordionItem>

          <AccordionItem class="mb-4" title="Who is this platform for?" variant="chevron">
            This platform is designed for educators, trainers, schools, and organizations working with children. It is especially valuable for teachers who do not have a background in cybersecurity but want to introduce digital safety topics in an engaging and age-appropriate way. Ultimately, the platform benefits children by helping them develop essential digital safety skills.
          </AccordionItem>

          <AccordionItem class="mb-4" title="How can I get involved?" variant="chevron">
            You can get involved by exploring our resources, participating in training activities, and sharing the materials within your educational community. Schools and organizations can collaborate with us, pilot the materials, or join dissemination activities. Together, we can strengthen cybersecurity education and create a safer digital environment for children across Europe.
          </AccordionItem>
        </Accordion>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>
</DefaultLayout>

<style>
  .section-badge {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
  }

  .section-icon {
    color: #fff;
    background-color: #2563eb;
    border-color: #2563eb;
    font-size: 2.5em;
    font-weight: bold;
  }

  .section-heading {
    font-size: clamp(4rem, 1.5rem + 1vw, 2.75rem);
    font-weight: 900;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-decoration-color: #2563eb;
    margin-bottom: 0.7rem;
  }

  .section-subtitle {
    color: var(--color-neutral-700);
    font-size: 1.15rem;
  }

  .value-grid :global(.card) {
    box-shadow: var(--elevation-2);
    transition: transform 0.25s ease, box-shadow 0.25s ease;
    border-color: #e2e8f0;
    background: var(--color-neutral-100);
  }

  .value-grid :global(.card:hover),
  .value-grid :global(.card:focus-within) {
    transform: translateY(-6px);
    box-shadow: var(--elevation-4);
    border-color: #2563eb;
  }
  
  :global(.value-feature [data-icon]) {
    color: #2563eb;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .section-badge {
      justify-content: flex-start;
    }
  }
</style>
